BSCcore
Interface ModelVisitor

All Known Implementing Classes:
HTMLTextRenderer, JSONRenderer, JUnitRenderer, KMLRenderer, SimpleTextRenderer, TestVisitor, TextRenderer, TextTreeRenderer, XSLRenderer
public interface ModelVisitor

This interface defines the methods that a class must implement to be able to use the visitor methods in BSCObject (e.g., visitDescendents()).

Method Summary

Method Detail

visitEnter

boolean visitEnter(BSCObject obj,
                   int depth,
                   int obj_cnt)
Notify the visitor that it is entering obj.

Parameters:
obj - The BSCObject this visitor is entering.
depth - The distance of obj from the BSCObject at which the traversal began.
obj_cnt - The position of obj among its siblings.
Returns:
Whether or not to continue the traversal at the next level (e.g., depth + 1) beyond obj.
